ident. And in these times, it is best to seek out guidance from experienced counsel who understand what you’re going through and have the professional knowledge to insure that the right steps are taken to protect you when you need it most. If you have been hurt, consider seeking direction and counsel from the experienced Lafayette personal injury attorneys of Broussard & David, LLC.Broussard & David, LLC has set the bar for full recovery in serious personal injury and wrongful death cases. The firm’s attorneys have gained state and national recognition for their achievement, service, and results.Founding partner Richard Broussard has spent his entire career dedicated to protecting the rights of people whose injuries have changed their lives. In addition to being recognized as a Super Lawyer, he was also selected in a statewide poll as one of the “Top 50” Lawyers in Louisiana. A Super Lawyer himself and recognized by the National Trial Lawyers Association as one of the “Top 100 Trial Lawyers,” founding partner Blake David has achieved state and national acclaim for his accomplishment in the courtroom. Among other verdicts, Lafayette personal injury lawyer Blake David has served as lead counsel on three wrongful death cases in the parishes of Lafayette, Calcasieu, and St. Charles in which the verdicts—$21 Million; $10.5 Million; and $29 Million—were the largest reported wrongful death awards in each respective parish's history. Further, Blake David has the highest recorded injury verdict in Lafayette Parish history - $30 Million.Broussard & David, LLC’s record of accomplishment and reputation for fighting to protect the rights of accident victims in and around Louisiana, with a concentration of cases in the Acadiana area, have given us the experience and resources to handle the most difficult cases from the date of the accident to verdict or settlement.Recovering Damages for Your Louisiana AccidentA person injured by the careless actions of another party may file a lawsuit based on negligence, which is the most common theory of recovery in personal injury lawsuits in Louisiana. The victim can prevail and hold the defendant liable by successfully proving each of the following four elements:The defendant owed the victim a duty of reasonable care;The defendant breached that duty;The breach caused the victim’s injury; andThe victim suffered damages as a result of the injury.Because of your accident, you may be eligible to recover money damages. Specifically, under Louisiana law, you may be entitled to compensation for your past and future medical bills; past and future lost earnings; loss of future earning capacity; and pain and suffering associated with the losses you have suffered. If you were injured as the result of a drunk driver or you were hurt offshore, you may be entitled to damages designed to punish the defendants for their reckless and wanton ways. Irrespective of how you or your loved one was hurt—offshore, in an auto accident, or a helicopter crash—let Broussard & David, LLC obtain justice for you and get you and your family the compensation that is deserved.Aggressive Legal Representation for Accident Victims in LouisianaWhile recovering from injuries that have changed your life, you should not be forced to wonder if you can pay the medical bills necessary for your treatment or how your missed work will affect your family and your future. The Lafayette personal injury lawyers of Broussard & David, LLC are ready to bring the full scope of our experience to hold the person or entity that hurt you accountable for their actions. There is no charge for our services unless and until we recover compensation for you through a settlement or verdict. Our clients span many parishes around Louisiana. We listen closely to the details of their situations and craft a legal strategy tailored to each client’s specific needs. Call (888) 337-2323 or complete our online form to schedule a free initial consultation with our attorneys.Boar